##Don't believe the Internet rumors, the real Italian epidemic is like this

WECHAT soulker 2017

Functional introduction to the supreme reading interest of the original content platform.

This article is about 3700 words long

Reading needs

8 min
At the beginning of this article, it is important to let the reader know that the author's story is by no means entirely credible.
I've lived in Italy for more than a decade, and I've been a journalist, and after this outbreak, I've been approached by a lot of media, and I've even been offered good money to tell the story of Italy's fight against the plague.
But do I know enough about the Italian epidemic? Just like each of you, whether or not you have enough knowledge of the Chinese epidemic experience? When disasters happen, people always want to have a general understanding in the shortest time, eager to establish a concise theory, but I am particularly wary of such a "reading consumption" .
The new coronavirus can cause such huge harm, its power does not lie entirely in its "toxicity" , but lies in its powerful camouflage. Perhaps that's the nature of the catastrophe itself.
In addition to declaring that what I've written isn't entirely believable, I hope you'll do your best to relax -- I'm in a relaxed mood. Just got back from walking the dog. I go out with two dogs once a day in the morning and once in the evening.
In the morning, the Tuscan Sun was so bright in March that I saw about a dozen people in the Park Square, at least 10 meters away from each other. Two homeless men who spend most of their nights on park benches, and when they see me coming, they start yelling from a distance.
Two dogs started shitting on the dead leaves, and I said to the homeless man, you guys are so immune, I've been sick a couple of times since last winter, and you're out here in the sun every day.
"because you don't drink, " one of them answered.
Go to the Park Plaza again at midnight, no one on the street, no car. Homeless people don't sleep on benches.
Suddenly, Florence is beautiful at night. Instead, I have an urgent article to write.
1

How Italy's epidemic disaster came to be, we first need to understand Italy's public health system.
The Sichuan team of medical experts came to Italy to talk about the rescue of the 2008 Sichuan earthquake in 2008,30 years after the Italian aid center was built. In many people's minds, "Italy" is a funny country, Italians always have too many romantic unruly behavior.
Italians at home perform a balcony concert on March 14,2020
VIDEO: Twitter@gabriele  
What they don't understand is that, despite having a large number of poor areas and a large number of poor people, Italy is one of the oldest countries in the world, and their public health care is among the highest in the world, first Aid is an Italian medical specialty.
I was healthy enough to come to Italy a few years ago without much exposure to the country's health care system, but I was exposed to something else I never imagined: Whether I was going to the gym or playing amateur football, I needed a medical certificate, different tests are needed depending on the type of activity, such as playing football, which requires a rigorous heart exam.
It is a move that the Italian medical community is proud of, which minimises the risk of sudden death from exercise, and which is paid for by the state.
In recent years, with the addition of children to our families, we have finally learned more about public health and hospitals in Italy. Foreigners like US, who normally pay taxes, are automatically included in their public health system, and the local health department sends the card home. The cost of seeing a family doctor, doing routine check-ups and buying medicine can be offset against the tax.
In the case of hospital admission, such as childbirth, or the previous daughter sick, the whole process does not cost a penny, and procedures, procedures are extremely simple, the signature of a nurse to take the form to the ward. Italian hospitals also provide patients with delicious meals, which are free of charge.
How about public health care? For those in need, of course. The quality of care is guaranteed, and the patient has no worries, will not be treated half because money is not enough to be driven away.
In the face of the Pandemic, the relationship between public health care and the nation has become a soft spot. Too many Italians do not mind sick, really not good, is not to a hospital bed a lie?
In my observations, this tendency is most pronounced after an outbreak. In late February, when the town of lombardy-cordonio hit its "tipping point, " several patients with mild cases of the disease emerged, eager to tell the public that it was a "minor cold. ". According to early statistics, mild and asymptomatic infection accounted for 80% of the population, no wonder the famous Italian virologist Gismundo also issued an oolong strange, "just a little more than the flu. ".
Maria Rita Gismondo, an Italian virologist, once declared that the new coronavirus was "just a little bit stronger than the flu" .
With the Italian economy heavily dependent on tertiary sector of the economy, the idea of a "pandemic" was immediately seized on by politicians such as far-right leader Salvini, whose party controls several regions in the north. At the end of February, Salvini could barely say one word: 'Go! Go! Go! ' As soon as the alarms went off, the city reopened, even throwing a 'Milan won't stop' themed Party to celebrate.
Milan will not stop promoting short films

It can be said that northern Italy has become a major disaster area, and the region's most developed economy, the most densely populated, the best medical conditions have a certain relationship. Hospital admissions for severe cases and home medication for mild cases are in themselves part of Italy's public health practice, and people have no concept of the collapse of medical resources, i didn't know that the newly-crowned patients occupied the beds much longer than other patients with acute diseases, despite the loud objections and warnings of many medical professionals.

2

Am I worried about the high mortality rate in Italy? I would like to provide the data as of yesterday: The average age of death in Italy's new crown is over 80, and there are only two deaths under the age of 50, of which one is on cancer treatment and the other is obese and diabetic.
At the same time, the Italians seem to have a loose nature, but the Down to Earth in some places is impressive, the fight against the plague is not about medals, the mortality rate is higher than in other places, and in the eyes of the Italian medical community, it's more about statistical differences.
A characteristic of the new coronavirus is easy to stimulate the body of other chronic diseases, including diabetes, hypertension, epilepsy and other diseases are known. A lot of acute death to the hospital soon after death, Italy will also give the deceased test paper, if it is also included in the statistics. The dead are also carefully examined because medical workers do not necessarily adopt a full set of high-level protective measures when rescuing patients whose pneumonia symptoms are not obvious. If the deceased is positive, health care workers need to go back through the process and decide whether to quarantine immediately.
According to viral and epidemiologic experts, NCP has been circulating in Italy since late January. Why wasn't Italy, the first European country to declare a national emergency, detected sooner? Would it have been better to have found Lombardi's breaking point a week or two in advance?
The question is based on a judicial inquiry. Italy's high level of public health care has to do with tight control over procedures. If there are consequences to a suspected process error, it automatically triggers a judicial investigation. Two years ago, for example, Captain Astorri of Florence died in his sleep, and the doctor who had given him his medical clearance was sent to prison because, according to the records, there was a partial abnormality on Astori's electrocardiogram, the doctors missed it.
The first two points of the Italian outbreak -- the town of Fo Cordoño and emergency centres in Vaux -- were the subject of a judicial inquiry, which found that the doctors were not at fault.
Having declared a national emergency, the Italian government knew the new crown would come. But they did not raise their standards for early warning and surveillance, and stuck to the TOCC (Travel, Office, Contact, Community) principle of dealing with infectious epidemics, with Contact or Travel history test strips. You might have missed a case earlier than "patient one. "
Thanks to the intuition of a female anesthesiologist at the CODOGNO emergency center, patient number one was able to show herself. She was so skeptical that she persisted in questioning the patient's family, the patient had previously had lunch with a manager back in China, which gave her a reason to test herself -- as if an outbreak in Italy had finally surfaced.
Patient 1's trajectory in Italy, source: thepaper.cn

In fact, the manager who was referred to as patient zero was negative and had no antibodies, not a carrier. According to virologists, the Italian virus was transmitted from Bavaria, Germany. That is to say, in Bavaria, after the first human-to-human outbreak in Europe, the spread had already begun, despite the harsh measures taken immediately by the Germans.

3

About a week ago, as the epidemics in France, Portugal and Spain were unfolding, I had a sudden feeling that Italy would be forgotten in the not too distant future. These countries will grab the headlines of the new outbreak. Still, Johnson is strong enough that his herd immunity theory will be the focus of intense debate around the world in the weeks and months ahead.
Herd Immunity
On March 12,2020, British Prime Minister Boris Johnson announced that the UK had entered the second phase of the fight against the pandemic, "delayed" (AFP) 
The Italian medical community reacted to the British move with fury, with some calling it outright barbarism.
One criticism of the Italian epidemic on the Chinese Internet is that Italian hospitals have left the elderly to fend for themselves. This is a misunderstanding.
Italy every day will release a complete regional epidemic data, interested friends can calculate their own, Italy's hospital admission rate is very high. At the same time, the Italian epidemic is a bit like the Italian football defense, dangerous but always find a way out. For example, the use of helicopters in the regions and even across the country to transfer the critically ill patients, rational deployment of the existing critical bed inventory, as far as the north from the affected area Bergamo transported to the south of Sicily, Palermo.
It is now almost a month since the outbreak began in Italy. In the most serious region of Lombardy, hospitals are still opening new critical beds and have not stopped treating other patients due to the new crown disease. I have to say, the Italians did a good job.
Claudio Furlanlapresseap, a temporary addition to an emergency ward at a hospital in Brescia, northern Italy
So how do rumors of abandonment of the elderly come about?
It is safe to say that if the Italian government or its affiliates demanded that hospitals give priority to young people, they would be immediately forced to resign in popular anger. That's not what happened.
This rumor is based on an Italian Association of anesthesiologists / Emergency Physicians'advice to its members during an outbreak, which suggests that patients can be selected without adhering to the first come, first served order, instead, priority is given to the expectation of first aid and to the survival of the patient after resuscitation.
The guidance does not come from government agencies or hospitals, but from professional industry associations; it is not a decree, but is intended only in the context of outbreaks and high levels of work, to ensure the efficiency of first aid and the psychological state of the emergency physician. An emergency physician has said that some novice often prone to mood swings, in fact, the usual first aid will have a similar principle, first aid is not unlimited use of medical resources and means to find "miracle. ".
Dr. Boutros Boutros-Ghali, director of the Sako Hospital in Milan, one of the largest specialist hospitals to admit new patients, said there was no such thing as patient selection, and "giving up patients" was purely a medical practice, "For example, if a patient has multiple underlying diseases, it's a mistake to go in either direction. ".
Dr. Boutros Boutros-Ghali was interviewed about the outbreak in Milan on March 3,2020
AFP via Getty Images, FILE

4

Finally, let's talk about something that gives people hope.
The Chinese medical community has shared with Italy the results of studies on the role of Tozumab in the prevention of new coronary pneumonia (NCP) . Clinical trials in Italian hospitals have been very successful, and it is expected that Tozumab will soon be introduced into the national new Crown Medical Program in Italy.
Radcivir, which has been tested in Italy before, has also received good clinical feedback on antiviral drugs.
What is really missing is a drug that can guarantee that most people with mild illness will not become severely ill. Only when the drug is found will life return to normal, and the new crown officially becomes a form of influenza.
Dear reader, please forgive me, the author can not help but pretend to understand the medical do not get up..

That is to say, in Bavaria, after the first human-to-human outbreak in Europe, the spread had already begun, despite the harsh measures taken immediately by the Germans.

3

About a week ago, as the epidemics in France, Portugal and Spain were unfolding, I had a sudden feeling that Italy would be forgotten in the not too distant future. These countries will grab the headlines of the new outbreak. Still, Johnson is strong enough that his herd immunity theory will be the focus of intense debate around the world in the weeks and months ahead.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Herd Immunity

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On March 12,2020, British Prime Minister Boris Johnson announced that the UK had entered the second phase of the fight against the pandemic, "delayed" (AFP) 

The Italian medical community reacted to the British move with fury, with some calling it outright barbarism.

One criticism of the Italian epidemic on the Chinese Internet is that Italian hospitals have left the elderly to fend for themselves. This is a misunderstanding.

Italy every day will release a complete regional epidemic data, interested friends can calculate their own, Italy's hospital admission rate is very high. At the same time, the Italian epidemic is a bit like the Italian football defense, dangerous but always find a way out. For example, the use of helicopters in the regions and even across the country to transfer the critically ill patients, rational deployment of the existing critical bed inventory, as far as the north from the affected area Bergamo transported to the south of Sicily, Palermo.

It is now almost a month since the outbreak began in Italy. In the most serious region of Lombardy, hospitals are still opening new critical beds and have not stopped treating other patients due to the new crown disease. I have to say, the Italians did a good job.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Claudio Furlanlapresseap, a temporary addition to an emergency ward at a hospital in Brescia, northern Italy

So how do rumors of abandonment of the elderly come about?

It is safe to say that if the Italian government or its affiliates demanded that hospitals give priority to young people, they would be immediately forced to resign in popular anger. That's not what happened.

This rumor is based on an Italian Association of anesthesiologists / Emergency Physicians'advice to its members during an outbreak, which suggests that patients can be selected without adhering to the first come, first served order, instead, priority is given to the expectation of first aid and to the survival of the patient after resuscitation.

The guidance does not come from government agencies or hospitals, but from professional industry associations; it is not a decree, but is intended only in the context of outbreaks and high levels of work, to ensure the efficiency of first aid and the psychological state of the emergency physician. An emergency physician has said that some novice often prone to mood swings, in fact, the usual first aid will have a similar principle, first aid is not unlimited use of medical resources and means to find "miracle. ".

Dr. Boutros Boutros-Ghali, director of the Sako Hospital in Milan, one of the largest specialist hospitals to admit new patients, said there was no such thing as patient selection, and "giving up patients" was purely a medical practice, "For example, if a patient has multiple underlying diseases, it's a mistake to go in either direction. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Dr. Boutros Boutros-Ghali was interviewed about the outbreak in Milan on March 3,2020

AFP via Getty Images, FILE

4

Finally, let's talk about something that gives people hope.

The Chinese medical community has shared with Italy the results of studies on the role of Tozumab in the prevention of new coronary pneumonia (NCP) . Clinical trials in Italian hospitals have been very successful, and it is expected that Tozumab will soon be introduced into the national new Crown Medical Program in Italy.

Radcivir, which has been tested in Italy before, has also received good clinical feedback on antiviral drugs.

What is really missing is a drug that can guarantee that most people with mild illness will not become severely ill. Only when the drug is found will life return to normal, and the new crown officially becomes a form of influenza.
